Bring a #large pot{} of @salt{} water to a boil. Wash and dry produce.

Peel and thinly slice @garlic{1%clove}. Trim and quarter @zucchini{1} lengthwise; cut crosswise into ½-inch-thick pieces. Zest and quarter @lemon{1}. Finely chop @parsley{¼%oz}.

Heat a drizzle of @olive oil{1%tsp} in a large, preferably #nonstick pan{} over medium heat. Add garlic and cook, stirring occasionally, until golden and fragrant, ~{1%minute}.

> Keep a close eye on the garlic to avoid burning. Remove from heat as soon as it turns a pale golden color.

Turn off heat; using a #slotted spoon{}, transfer garlic to a #paper-towel-lined plate{}. Wipe out pan.

Once water is boiling, add @penne pasta{6%oz} to #pot{}. Cook, stirring occasionally, until al dente, ~{9-11%minutes}.

Reserve 1 cup pasta cooking water, then drain and set aside.

While pasta cooks, heat a drizzle of @cooking oil{2%tsp} in pan used for garlic over medium-high heat. Add zucchini and cook, stirring, until tender and lightly golden, ~{5-6%minutes}. Season with @salt{} and @pepper{}.

Transfer to a #plate{}.

While zucchini cooks, pat @shrimp{10%oz} dry with #paper towels{}; season with salt and pepper.

Once zucchini is done, heat a drizzle of oil in same pan over medium-high heat. Add shrimp in a single layer and cook, stirring occasionally, until opaque and cooked through, ~{4-6%minutes}. Reduce heat to medium.

Stir in @cream sauce base{4%oz}, ¼ cup reserved pasta cooking water, and a big squeeze of lemon juice; cook, stirring occasionally, until thickened, ~{2-3%minutes}.

> If sauce seems too thick, stir in another splash or two of pasta cooking water.

Add drained penne, toasted garlic, zucchini, half the @Parmesan cheese{3%tbsp}, half the parsley, half the lemon zest (use all the zest if desired), and @butter{2%tbsp} to pan with sauce. Toss to combine. Season with salt and pepper.

> If needed, stir in more pasta cooking water a splash at a time until everything is coated in a creamy sauce.

Divide pasta between #bowls{}. Top with remaining Parmesan and remaining parsley. Serve with remaining lemon wedges on the side.

> Shrimp are fully cooked when internal temperature reaches 145°.